Context:
- Codebase is a React + TypeScript + Leaflet geolocation app; mock sensor data is generated in hooks/useSensorData.ts and rendered via MapComponent/Sidebar/DetailsPanel.
- Postman collection to follow: API Monitoring TMAT - Portal V1 (Frontend-Public Key).postman_collection.json (key endpoints: GET /perusahaan, GET /perusahaan?id={{id_perusahaan}}, GET /site?id_perusahaan={{id_perusahaan}}, GET /site?id=..., GET /device, GET /device?device_id=..., GET /realtime_all?id_perusahaan={{id_perusahaan}}, GET /realtime_device?device_id={{deviceId}}&start_date=...&end_date=...&limit=...; see lines 10-259). Use variables {{baseUrl}} and header X-API-KEY: {{portalApiKey}}.

Goals:
1) Add a UI toggle “Use mock data” (on by default). When on, keep using the existing generated data; when off, fetch from the APIs above.
2) Introduce data fetch and caching layers for:
   - Company list (“Daftar Perusahaan”): GET /perusahaan; detail via GET /perusahaan?id=...
   - Site list (“Daftar Site”): GET /site?id_perusahaan={{id_perusahaan}} (filter by company); detail via GET /site?id=...
   - Device list (“Daftar Device”): GET /device (all) and GET /device?device_id={{deviceId}} (detail).
   - Realtime summaries: GET /realtime_all?id_perusahaan={{id_perusahaan}} for overview; GET /realtime_device?device_id={{deviceId}}&start_date=...&end_date=...&limit=... for time-series.
3) Map the API responses into the existing SensorDataPoint shape (lat, lng, waterLevel, status, lastUpdated, deviceId, etc.). If backend fields differ, add adapters so the UI stays unchanged.
4) Expose UI panels/tabs for:
   - Company list and detail (select company → filters sites/devices).
   - Site list and detail (show location, owned devices).
   - Device list and detail (metadata + last update).
   - Realtime data (summary cards and per-device charts/tables for the selected period).
5) Error/loading handling: show spinners/placeholders; on fetch failure, fall back to mock data with a warning; respect the mock/live toggle.
6) Config: read {{baseUrl}} and {{portalApiKey}} from env (e.g., Vite env vars). Centralize API client with shared headers.
7) Keep TypeScript types in types.ts up to date (new interfaces for Company, Site, Device, RealtimeSummary, RealtimePoint) and reuse across components.
8) Add minimal tests or story-style fixtures for both mock and API data paths; ensure the toggle path is covered.

Deliverables:
- Updated components/hooks to support the toggle and new data sources.
- New UI for company/site/device/realtime data browsers integrated with the map selection.
- Docs in README about configuring env vars and how the mock/live toggle works.
